# =============================================================================
# Risk Game - Environment Configuration
# =============================================================================
#
# Quick Start:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local:
#    cp .env.example .env.local
#
# 2. Choose ONE of these options:
#
#    OPTION A: Mock Mode (Offline Development - Recommended for trying out the app)
#    Set NEXT_PUBLIC_MOCK_MODE=true and skip Supabase setup
#
#    OPTION B: Real Supabase (Full Functionality)
#    Create a Supabase project and fill in credentials below
#
# See QUICKSTART.md for detailed setup instructions
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Mock Mode (Optional - Enables offline development without Supabase)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Uncomment to use mock data instead of real Supabase
# Perfect for quick exploration without setup
# Note: Realtime features will use polling instead of WebSockets
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_MOCK_MODE=true

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Supabase Configuration (Required if NOT using mock mode)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Get your credentials from: https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/_/settings/api
#
# IMPORTANT: Variables MUST start with NEXT_PUBLIC_ to work in the browser
#
# Project URL format: https://xxxxxxxxxxxxx.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
#
# Anon Key (safe to expose in browser - respects RLS policies)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here
#
# After adding credentials:
# 1. Run the schema migration (copy SQL from supabase-schema.sql to Supabase SQL Editor)
# 2. Enable Realtime for tables: games, players, territories, game_actions
#    (Database → Replication → Enable for each table)
# 3. Start dev server: npm run dev

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Node Environment
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
NODE_ENV=development
